article.headline: Lehigh 73, Columbia 59
article.story: BETHLEHEM, Pa. -- Zahir Carrington scored 21 points and Bob Keefer added 20 as Lehigh overcame an early 15-point deficit and beat Columbia 73-59 Friday. Keefer shot 7-for-10 from the field, including 4-for-4 from 3-point range, and Marquis Hall added 12 points for Lehigh (10-3). Joe Bova and Niko Scott each scored 10 points for Columbia (4-8), which shot 38 percent (23-for-60) from the field, including 6-for-24 from long range. Columbia raced to a 17-2 lead in the first six minutes. Lehigh countered with a 29-8 scoring run through the rest of the first half and held a six-point lead, 31-25, at the break. Lehigh sealed the win by outscoring Columbia 42-34 in the second half.
